If I correctly understood, you need to print 

 - Sum of all positive numbers
 - Sum of all negative numbers
 - And Sum of all numbers.
 - Re run the program if needed by the user.



For all the desired output you have to do following:

 - Make user enter only 10 number, which is handled by a variable totalInput and of course some input handling class.In this case I have used Scanner. 
 - While traversing the input from the user, validate if is positive or negative and accordingly update the sumPositive or sumNegative variables.
 - And at last for printing the total sum you can add both sumPositive and sumNegative to display the total sum.
 - For re running you can take the advantage of do while loop and after one iteration of user input, you can take his input, validate it and perform re run if required or exit.


````
import java.util.Scanner;
public class Main
{
    static Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	    String choice=null;
	   	do
	   	{
	   	    calculateSum();
	   	    System.out.println(&quot;If you wish to continue, Press Yes&quot;);
	   	    choice = sc.next();
	   	}
	   	while(choice.equals(&quot;Yes&quot;));
	   	sc.close();
	}
	
	static void calculateSum()
	{
	     int totalInput=0,sumPositive=0,sumNegative=0;
		
		System.out.println(&quot;start entering your numbers&quot;);
		while(totalInput &lt; 10)
		{
		    int num=sc.nextInt();
		    if(num&gt;0)
		    {
		        sumPositive+=num;
		    }
		    else
		        sumNegative+=num;
		        
		    totalInput++;
		}
		System.out.println(&quot;The sum of all positive numbers is &quot; +sumPositive);
		System.out.println(&quot;The sum of all negative numbers is &quot; +sumNegative);
		System.out.println(&quot;The total sum is &quot; +(sumPositive + sumNegative));
	
	}
}

